{
 "name": "RPlog_Triumphant_Return_or_Maybe_Not",
 "title": "Triumphant Return, or Maybe Not: The Wings of Justice",
 "summary": "Having stolen the experimental Imperial Victory-class Star Destroyer Wings of Justice, the Chyleni pilot Kyrin Sh'vani is found in the Deep Core by the Jedi Brandis Finian, who tracked her through the Force; the two reunite joyfully and jump the prize ship back toward the New Republic fleet at Coruscant. Their arrival triggers a tense standoff as the NRSD Reprisal scrambles fighters and Marines under Commander Gorrman to escort the captured ship, the Imperial Broadsword under Captain Caiton maneuvers to destroy it, and starfighter squadrons from both sides clash in the surrounding space. A New Republic Marine boarding party led by Wrista Ipex secures the bridge with the technician Mitali, but a fanatical captive Imperial tech sabotages the engines into a self-destruct overload before being cut down. Kyrin orders an evacuation, and Brandis hustles her aboard his freighter as the Wings of Justice explodes spectacularly, its shockwave scattering both fleets. Brandis bears the exhausted Kyrin not to the Reprisal but to Coruscant to rest, while she insists she must brief the admiral on what she learned.",
